	<h2><TMPL_VAR NAME="PAGE_TITLE"> Tips</h2>
	<p><strong>LexisNexis Carrier ID provides insurance verification based on accident data and insurance carriers listed on accident reports. Carrier ID can be searched through a VIN or Name and Address search.</strong></p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>Search methods include:</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>VIN-</b></p>
	<p>Required fields are VIN and Claim #. The Date of Loss field is highly recommended and entering a date of loss greatly enhances search results. </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p> You must enter information in the required fields. </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>-- OR --</b></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>Name and Address-</b></p>
	<p>
        <p>First and Last Name are required fields PLUS one other group of fields are required in a combination as follows:</p>
	<ol id="font81">
        <li>Address(Street, City, State and Zip)</li>
        <li>SSN</li>
        <li>Drivers license # and Drivers license State</li>
        <li>DOB</li>
        </ol>
        <p> Entering the DOL greatly enhances the search results.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p> You must enter information in the required fields. </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>Please see the <a style="cursor: help;" href="javascript:void(0);" onClick="open_help('carrier_id_help.html');"><u><b>Help Page</b></u></a> for much more information on how to best utilize this powerful report.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
